originalText.text: I have used babies getaway in different states for car seat rentals since we travel a lot. Any issues customer service is there to help and they most of the times items were brand new. Amazing service. We already have a rental ongoing with them!

originalText.text:
I placed an order over a month before my trip to New Mexico.  I got a call the day before my trip that nothing I ordered was going to be available.  After multiple phone conversations and me asking if anything can be done, they agreed to order items at a local Walmart and I pick it up.  I was not able to get mattresses for my 2 kids and half the other items were not able to be ordered.  The pack and plays were compact and way to small to sleep in and once I was done with everything, I left them outside the rental property for pickup only to be told, on my way to the airport, that they can not pick the items up that day.  I am in a fight for a refund (at the very least the items I was not able to get but paid for) and they said they will give me one once the items are picked up.  I had to then fight for them to resolve this since it has now been multiple days without them getting the items.  They now say that the homeowner (AirBnB) can just keep the items or donate them.  They closed out my case and did not reflect any refund on the order even after days for trying to get a resolution.  DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY!!!!  They literally do not care if you get your rental items and were so incompetent and unprofessional through every single step of the process.

Edit: after seeing their response:
1. Items were “missed” on pickup day?  They didn’t even show up.
3. I did NOT initiate a chargeback! I asked for the refund and that is it!

originalText.text:
Before you place an order you should know...

You can do the same thing this company does...But a LOT cheaper.
I Will explain.

Walmart offers home delivery and returns.

This company opened a Walmart delivery account.

You place an order with them, they place an order with Walmart,  a few day a later they request a Walmart home return  and charge you $$$$$$$$
So if you pay the $10 to get Walmart delivery,  you can just order a return without paying a 3rd party???$$$$$$

I don't know if what this company does is legal...but it's an easy way to make a bunch of money without working.
